name: active_record
description: PHP ActiveRecord with focus on OO supporting subqueries, grouping and infinite joins. Not quite as powerful as something like Doctrine but no where near the amount of code either. The intial purpose of this was to eliminate the need to write queries ever again. While I will say it eliminates the need to write *many queries some things are not supported, yet like trees and unions. Those would require custom SQL. The current capabilities provide means of doing just about everything besides those things. The project itself was inspired by the PHPActiveRecord with an intention of providing a more powerful set of options but that was 3 years ago. Special note here is that this project is not meant to support virtual relational database modules like those present in Drupal w/ Fields. If you need to support those things this project is not for you. This project is intended to work with actual relational database schemas, not virual ones. Supporting virtual table schemas is a whole other ball game and one best avoided really. The one thing I regret and have learned from this project is comment and comment often. Sadely at the time of writing most of this I didn't think it was that important and it is one thing I wish I could have changed.
